API - Application Programming Interface.
JSON & XML are light weight and standard procedure to exchange information. 
2 ways we can communicate with webservices
using REST - widely used now (Representational state transfer) Architechtural design
using SOAP - old technology ( Simple object application protocol) protcol
REST uses JAX-RS Java API, its very light weight can use REST and SOAP as it is a pattern. 
can communicate with API using JSON and XML formats.
SOAP uses JAX-WS Java API, Its very weight protocol, uses more bandwidth can communicate with XML format only 
CRUD Operations 
C - Create - POST CALL 
R - Retrieve - GET CALL 
U - Update - PUT CALL
D - Delete - DELETE CALL 
SWagger tool  - API Documentation

